**Overall Meaning:**

This verse highlights the profound impact of performing rituals with knowledge and understanding. It states:

"Then he who, knowing this thus, offers the agnihotra, his offering becomes offered in all worlds, in all beings, in all souls."

This verse implies that when someone offers a ritual with true knowledge, the offering transcends the physical act and reaches a universal level. It becomes a universal offering, benefiting all worlds, beings, and souls. 

The verse emphasizes the transformative power of knowledge and the interconnectedness of all existence.  It suggests that rituals performed with understanding have the potential to benefit not only the individual performing them but also the entire universe. 
